Today we walk for those that feel like they’re alone and are having a hard time seeing the light at the end of the tunnel.  I’m reminded today of my journey with Epilepsy since I was 17 and how God has shaped me THROUGH it and the ways he’s working through me.  Thank you Jesus for using me as a vessel. 

Check out the Walk Into It Podcast and join me in helping to spread more awareness and helping us find a cure for the disease that affects me and 65 million others like me. 

#EpilepsyWalkLA #epilepsy #epilepsyawareness  #epilepsyfoundation #WalkIntoItPodcast #educationiselevation #djlife🎧

Excited to share with you the Walk Into It Podcast, supported by the Epilepsy Foundation of Los Angeles! I know how important it is to raise awareness and spread education about epilepsy. The Walk Into It Podcast features inspiring stories from people who have overcome epilepsy, live with epilepsy and much more. With your support, we can help break down the stigma and create a more inclusive world for those living with epilepsy. You can find the podcast on ALL streaming platforms. So please check out the Walk Into It Podcast and share it with your friends and family! 

#WalkIntoItPodcast #epilepsy #epilepsyawareness #epilepsyfoundationoflosangeles #endepilepsy #educationiselevation #djlife🎧

Happy 50th birthday to Hip Hop!  Can’t even fully verbalize how important this movement and culture is to me and to millions of others that found their voice and their tribe through the elements.  Still in awe listening and watching the legends perform #hiphop #50hiphopanniversary #sugarhillgang #rappersdelight

I don’t know if anyone else remembers this but…Back in 2010, I had the opportunity to meet Kool Herc at what I believe was @boomboxla in Chinatown.  I was running @scratchla at the time and whispered to @officialtlopez “what if we invited him to come to Scratch?!” She made the intro, I met Herc and in less than 15 hours he was standing on our stage 🤯 @therealmrchoc and I interviewed him, presented him with some handwritten heartfelt messages from students and the community along with a custom wood carving from our in house designer B COLEY and tried our best to make the man responsible for opening up the doors of DJing, MCing, BBoying feel at home and honored.  Today marks 50 years since that party in the Bronx where @officialdjkoolherc extended the break to keep the kids dancing and paved the way for this culture (DJing AND Hip Hop) that I love to my core.  Forever grateful and if you EVER get a chance to shake this man’s huge hand, drop everything you’re doing and do it!  #hiphop #50hiphopanniversary #koolherc
